1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 What is State Legislature?

The State Legislature makes laws for the state.

States may have:

1️⃣ Unicameral Legislature

Only Legislative Assembly

OR

2️⃣ Bicameral Legislature

Legislative Assembly + Legislative Council

📌 Most Indian states are unicameral.

🔵 Legislative Assembly (Vidhan Sabha)
Lower House
Directly elected by people
Features:
Real legislative power
Money Bills introduced only here
Term:
5 years
Presiding Officer:
Speaker
🔴 Legislative Council (Vidhan Parishad)
Upper House
Permanent body
Features:
Cannot be dissolved
One-third members retire every 2 years
Term of Members:
6 years
Presiding Officer:
Chairman

📌 Legislative Council exists only in some states.

🔹 Creation & Abolition of Legislative Council

Parliament can create or abolish Legislative Council if:

State Assembly passes resolution by special majority

📌 Article 169.

🔹 Composition of Legislative Council

Members elected from:

Local bodies
Teachers
Graduates
Legislative Assembly
Nominated by Governor

📌 Important UPSC factual area.

🔹 Difference Between Assembly & Council
Feature	Assembly	Council
Nature	Temporary	Permanent
Election	Direct	Indirect
Power	More	Less
Money Bill	Major role	Limited role
🔹 Important Facts
Legislative Council is weaker than Assembly
Assembly controls executive through no-confidence motion
